 implementation. [[User:Whouk|Whouk]] <small>([[User talk:Whouk|talk]])</small> 12:47, 7 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Oppose''' I forgot I even had it enabled, but in the past I've accidentally clicked it when I wanted to edit the whole article.  New editors and anons will be even more confused by this.&nbsp;[[User:Ryan Vesey|'''''Ryan''''']]&nbsp;[[User talk:Ryan Vesey|'''''Vesey''''']] 13:12, 7 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' I find this tool to be quite useful. It helps lessen edit conflicts as well.--[[User:TonyTheTiger|TonyTheTiger]] <small>([[User talk:TonyTheTiger|T]]/[[Special:Contributions/TonyTheTiger|C]]/[[User:TonyTheTiger/Antonio Vernon|BIO]]/[[WP:CHICAGO]]/[[WP:FOUR]]) </small> 13:34, 7 August 2012 (UTC) * '''Oppose''' I've personally turned this gadget on, but in practice I just click the edit (whole page) button if I want to edit a lead section. It's perhaps useful for experienced editors, not so much for new ones and&mdash;especially with the longer caption&mdash;adds whole lot of unnecessary clutter to the interface. Just leave it as an opt-in. —''[[User:Ruud Koot|Ruud]]'' 14:09, 4 August 2012 (UTC) ** '''N.B.''' This gadget is especially confusing if the lead section is long enough that the edit links on actual sections are not immediately visible on (sufficiently small) screen(s). E.g., today's featured article: [[Peveril Castle]]. Even with the longer caption proposed below new editors are still likely to confuse this for a "edit whole page" button, due to a lack of context. I also fail to see the actual benefit of editing the lead section over editing the whole page; as far as I'm aware it does ''not'' reduce edit conflicts. —''[[User:Ruud Koot|Ruud]]'' 19:44, 7 August 2012 (UTC) ** '''Comment''' I do think we should make the "Edit" button/tab more prominent, e.g. by making the link bold or giving it a slightly darker background than the other buttons/tabs. —''[[User:Ruud Koot|Ruud]]'' 14:13, 4 August 2012 (UTC) ***If I understand this search correctly ([http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3ASearch&profile=advanced&search=%22ca-edit%22&fulltext=Search&ns8=1&redirs=1&profile=advanced "ca-edit" in Mediawiki space]) the value given in the Monobook.css would need to be copied over to [[MediaWiki:Vector.css]]. -- [[User:Quiddity|Quiddity]] ([[User talk:Quiddity|talk]]) 07:47, 15 August 2012 (UTC) *'''comment''', I've added threads at [[MediaWiki talk:Gadget-edittop]] and [[MediaWiki talk:Gadget-edittop.js#Village pump Proposals - Wording and Default|.js]], linking here and summarizing a few points. -- [[User:Quiddity|Quiddity]] ([[User talk:Quiddity|talk]]) 07:36, 15 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' I used the gadget for a long time until it became buggy for me, maybe because of other gadgets. I'd love seeing it back. &ndash; [[User:Sgeureka|sgeureka]] <sup>[[User_talk:Sgeureka|t]]•[[Special:Contributions/Sgeureka|c]]</sup> 08:22, 15 August 2012 (UTC)  === Activate reworded section 0 edit link ===  Many of the above objections refer to confusion from inexperienced editors clicking <nowiki>[</nowiki>[[#Activate reworded section 0 edit link|edit]]<nowiki>]</nowiki> at the top expecting to be able to edit the entire article, not only the lede. So, what if the text for this link were amended to make it less ambiguous before making it appear by default? — [[User:Richardguk|Richardguk]] ([[User talk:Richardguk|talk]]) 12:31, 4 August 2012 (UTC)  '''Refined proposal: Change the lede edit link text to <nowiki>[</nowiki>[[#Activate reworded section 0 edit link|edit intro]]<nowiki>]</nowiki> before making it appear by default.'''  * '''Support''' as proposer of the revised link text. — [[User:Richardguk|Richardguk]] ([[User talk:Richardguk|talk]]) 12:31, 4 August 2012 (UTC) * '''Support''' - also useful for those editors who choose not, or forget, to use an edit summary. [[User:Martinevans123|Martinevans123]] ([[User talk:Martinevans123|talk]]) 12:32, 4 August 2012 (UTC) *: The edit section 0 gadget does not generate an automatic edit summary? —''[[User:Ruud Koot|Ruud]]'' 19:47, 7 August 2012 (UTC) * '''Support''' new proposal. <font color="#151B8D">'''[[User:Rcsprinter123|<span style="font-family:cambria; font-size:10pt; color:#151B8D">Rcsprinter</span>]]''' [[User talk:Rcsprinter123|<span style="font-family:calibri; font-size:8pt; color:#488AC7">(babble)</span>]]</font> <small>@</small> 13:48, 5 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' Cuts the confusion.&nbsp;[[User:Ryan Vesey|'''''Ryan''''']]&nbsp;[[User talk:Ryan Vesey|'''''Vesey''''']] 13:12, 7 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support.''' "Edit intro" eliminates any confusion about what one is going to edit by clicking that link. --[[User:Timeshifter|'''Timeshifter''']] ([[User talk:Timeshifter|talk]]) 06:00, 8 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' This would make it clearer what that edit link is for. -- [[User:Toshio Yamaguchi|Toshio Yamaguchi]] ([[User talk:Toshio Yamaguchi|tlk]]−[[Special:Contributions/Toshio_Yamaguchi|ctb]]) 12:15, 9 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' I already use the gadget, and it's helpful occasionally. Renaming it "edit intro" will remove any misinterpretations. There's no consequences for making it default (with an opt-out button), so why not? '''''<font style="font-variant:small-caps;">[[User:Little Mountain 5|<font color="black">Little</font>]][[User talk:Little Mountain 5|<font color="red">Mountain</font>]][[Special:Contribs/Little Mountain 5|<font color="darkblue">5</font>]]</font>''''' 16:04, 14 August 2012 (UTC) * '''Support''' Makes it easier to edit. [[User:David1217|<span style="color:darkblue">'''David'''</span>]][[User talk:David1217|<span style="color:darkgreen">'''1217'''</span>]] <sup>[[Special:Contributions/David1217|<span style="color:black">'''''What I've done'''''</span>]]</sup> 16:15, 14 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''': why not? <span style="font-variant:small-caps">[[User:Thine Antique Pen (public)|<span style="color:#800">Thine</span>]] [[User talk:Thine Antique Pen (public)|<span style="color