 for creation. [[User:Kumioko|Kumioko]] ([[User talk:Kumioko|talk]]) 23:38, 11 August 2012 (UTC) * '''Support''' Sounds like a good idea to me! &bull; [[User:Jesse V.|Jesse V.]][[User talk:Jesse V.|<sup>''(talk)''</sup>]] 04:37, 12 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Comment''' I'm supportive of both these additions. ''Article creation wizard'' is self-explanatory, but I'm wondering if new users will know that ''Teahouse'' is a place to get help. [[Special:Contributions/64.40.54.58|64.40.54.58]] ([[User talk:64.40.54.58|talk]]) 14:06, 12 August 2012 (UTC) :Thats a good point. I think we could put something like Help - Teahouse to clarify. [[User:Kumioko|Kumioko]] ([[User talk:Kumioko|talk]]) 14:08, 12 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' with "Help - Teahouse" as suggested by Kumioko. <span style="font-variant:small-caps">[[User:Thine Antique Pen (public)|<span style="color:#800">Thine</span>]] [[User talk:Thine Antique Pen (public)|<span style="color:#006">Antique</span>]] [[Special:Contribs/Thine Antique Pen (public)|<span style="color:#330">Pen</span>]] [[Wikipedia:SOCK#LEGIT|<span style="color:#606">(public)</span>]]</span> 14:11, 12 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' - Both additions would be helpful to new editors without being intrusive.  [[User:Ebikeguy|Ebikeguy]] ([[User talk:Ebikeguy|talk]]) 16:02, 12 August 2012 (UTC) *'''Support''' Can't hurt. Or "Need Help? Visit Teahouse" but that's too long I guess :) [[User:SarahStierch|SarahStierch]] ([[User talk:SarahStierch|talk]]) 16:15, 12 August 2012 (UTC) *Interesting thoughts. You might want to ping [[Mediawiki talk:Sidebar]] also. --[[User:Izno|Izno]] ([[User talk:Izno|talk]]) 23:51, 12 August 2012 (UTC) **Kumioko went there [[MediaWiki_talk:Sidebar#Recommendation_for_a_couple_more_links|first]] ;) -- [[User:Quiddity|Quiddity]] ([[User talk:Quiddity|talk]]) 08:13, 13 August 2012 (UTC) * '''Reservations''': To quote: two of the most common questions I get are "How do I create an article?" and "How do I get help from experienced 